The evidence with the title 'Black progress: how far we've come, and how far we have to go ' says In a 1991 Gallup poll, about one-fifth of all whites, but almost half of black respondents , said that at least three out of four African Americans were impoverished urban residents .  ... When Gunnar Myrdal published An American Dilemma in 1944 , most blacks lived in the South and on the land as laborers and sharecroppers . 
